summary:
Providing exceptional Project and Program Management as a PMI certified Project Management Professional (PMP). Specializing in scope management, contractual negotiation, contract review, cost containment and process efficiency. 

Working within the B2B market with a wide range of government, industrial, corporate and fortune 500 companies.

Specialties: Operations strategy development, resource planning, performance monitor and improvement, implement operational processes and policies, relationship management, contract negotiation, cost containment / reduction specialist, staff management, strategic operational planning, tender submissions and support, contract administration, sales reporting, business development and key account management.

projects.title: Kronos Time & Attendance integration, roll-out and training
projects.description:
Testing, Training and Assisting the global project team with the roll-out of Kronos time and attendance software across 31 medical staffing sites including support materials. 
Hosting meetings and delivering project schedules to the global team to ensure performance of the Australasian region.

profile_positions.description:
The TRICARE Overseas Program in the Asia Pacific which serves TRICARE beneficiaries, MTF Stakeholders, and TRICARE Government stakeholders. Comprised of 9 time zones and 25 Countries and US Territories, the Asia Pacific Area of Responsibility includes 7 Military Hospitals and 10 Major Clinics along with over 40 Remote Sites. TRICARE is the health care program serving United States Uniformed Service members, retirees, and their families worldwide

Key Performance Requirements:-
* Delivery of all program management functions within the TRICARE Pacific Area of Responsibility 
* Support the Global Program Management Officer (PMO) in the development and review of operational objectives to meet the scope of the project. 
* Provision of TRICARE Program Management assistance to regional client stakeholders through project management / coordination, and liaison for issue resolution and for ensuring all standards and metrics in the TRICARE contract. 
* Delivery TOP contract services across the Pacific Region to TRIACRE beneficiary's, and TRICARE government stakeholders 
* Assist and manage necessary government audits in line with contractual requirements
profile_positions.title: TRICARE Deputy Program Director, Asia Pacific

profile_positions.description:
Site Liaison Manager for Australasia supporting Australia, New Zealand, Manus (Papua New Guinea) and Nauru / Christmas Islands. Leading a dedicated team of Site Liaison personnel to perform contractual requirements and objectives of Government, Corporate and Industrial clients. 

Key Objectives:-
* Implementation of Regional operational rostering, time and attendance and payroll software to all remote site locations in Australasia in line with PMO requirements. 
* Ensuring delivery of contractual scope within time, cost and resource containment 
* Working with internal and external stakeholders to implement corporate and contractual practices
* Review and implementation of process and SOP guidelines for operational best in class 
* Management and coaching of team members 
* Supporting medical staffing deployments for International SOS and IHMS. 
* Operations, Travel and Contractual Management.
profile_positions.title: Australasian Site Liaison Manager

profile_positions.description:
International Health and Medical Services manages health systems on behalf of governments and international organisations. We provide healthcare in both remote and urban settings, delivering a consistent standard of care even in physically and culturally challenging environments. 

Key Performance:-
* Management and performance appraisal of the Site Liaison team
* Effectively working with internal and external stakeholders across a number of countries 
* Ensuring contractual compliance with network providers (Travel agencies, accommodation, flight)
* Providing effective cost containment and reduction strategies in line with business requirements
* Strong stakeholder engagement with experience dealing with senior executives and front line staff requiring an adaptive and custom style to achieve required outcomes
* Understanding the strategic objectives of the business to develop operational processes to achieve same
* Development and implementation of guidelines and processes to ensure team has aligned with contractual and business requirements
* Continual improvement monitoring and organisational planning
profile_positions.title: Site Liaison Manager - IHMS

profile_positions.description:

* Process improvement
